title: For Sale:  Mech Tech .45 ACP CCU
postcontent:
Mech Tech CCU in .45 ACP, converts your Glock 20/21 into a carbine using your Glock lower and a Glock Block. This one has the M4 stock conversion for AR type stocks. Stainless inside and out, recessed crown. I have shot this exactly 230 times, fun to shoot and very lite recoil.
For any questions you may have as I have been getting quite a few.

C.C.U. Upper for Glock is available for the following Glock models: 
'SF' models - (All Gens)

G17; G17C; G34; G19; G19C; G20; G20C; G40; G21; G21C; G41; G22; G35; G22C; G23; G23C; G31; G32; G32C and the respective 'SF' models - (All Gens)

NOTE: Factory Loaded Ammunition Only. Mech Tech recommends only using good quality factory loaded ammunition in the CCU which meets SAAMI, CIP or NATO standards. The CCU is a blowback operated action and is capable of safely firing ammunition up to +P. DO NOT USE +P+ or 'hotter' loads.




NOTES FOR CCU's WHICH FIT GLOCKS

The CCU's fit Glock frames that are Compact (G19, G23, G32), Standard (G17, G22, G31, G34, G35) and Large (G20, G40, G21, G41). Mech Tech Uppers are not available for sub-compact Glocks. An interesting fact relates to Glock magazines. A frame separated from the slide and barrel will physically accept a magazine of a cartridge different from that for which the assembled pistol is designed (using magazines designed for the same series of frame sizes). What this means is that a Glock pistol & CCU combination can be set up to safely fire a cartridge different from that for which the assembled pistol is designed. Example: The frame (lower unit) of a Glock designed to fire the 45 ACP cartridge in the assembled pistol can be safely used with a CCU Upper designed to fire the 10mm cartridge. This is accomplished by assembly of the 45 ACP Glock frame to the 10mm CCU and the use of a Glock 10mm magazine designed to be used with that series of frame size. This information is provided only to illustrate the flexibility of the Mech Tech CCU. (Caution: the foregoing does not imply that a Glock pistol designed for a given cartridge can safely shoot a different cartridge by simply switching the magazine - this is dangerous - do not try it! Likewise a CCU Upper can safely fire only the cartridge for which it is designed!) If further clarification is needed please contact Mech Tech Systems Inc. 

NOTE: 357 Sig - this is a bottle necked cartridge. The CCU is a blowback action and therefore will work the brass during firing causing the shoulder to be set considerably forward. Re-loading the brass works the brass even more and may result in case separation when firing. Mech Tech has a 'factory ammo only' policy for all cartridges. 

Note: the CCU is not associated with Glock or endorsed by Glock - it is designed and manufactured in the USA.

The Rhino will accept any night vision device or adapter with a standard bayonet interface. The arm articulates with a “force to overcome” motion meaning the user simply pushes the device upward or down into position.

Standard issue USGI “J-Arm’s” are used to adapt the PVS-14 Night Vision Monocular to the standard issue USGI Rhino Mount. This gives the J-Arm the ability to shut down power to the night vision device when the user flips the Rhino Mount up; saving battery power, and limiting visibility of the green glow emitted from the ocular lens of the PVS-14.

For sale is a S&W Model 25-2 chambered in 45 ACP. This is an earlier one with the desirable 6 1/2" barrel, before they went to the 6" barrel. This revolver is in great shape and includes the original box, cleaning kit, paperwork, and sight adjustment tool. This is an interesting gun since standard 25-2's came with the target hammer and target trigger, however this one wears a standard hammer and standard trigger. Most folks would assume those parts had been swapped somewhere along the way yet, because this gun has it's original box, you can clearly see that it was special ordered with the standard components. Someone must've preferred the standard parts and had this one custom ordered from S&W; a decision I very much agree with!

PLEASE NOTE: The photos depict the revolver with the incorrect "Coke Bottle" stocks. These do NOT come with the gun. The gun will be provided wearing it's original football-cutout N-Frame target stocks. The Coke's are available if desired, but are $500 extra.

title: For Sale:  *MATCHING VET BRINGBACK* 1939 K98 Mauser 8MM "27" Code
postcontent:
*MATCHING VET BRINGBACK* 1939 K98 Mauser 8MM "27" Code

This is as original as it gets. Completely matching and unmolested 1939 date 27 code K98 Mauser with low serial number 194i. This is original down to the L&F 1939 dated sling, and even have the original cleaning kit issued with the gun in its original leather pouch. Also comes with a factory 1939 8mm ammo box.
Code 27 was formerly S27, which stood for Erfurter Maschinenfabrik (Erma). The receiver, barrel, rear sight group, bolt group including firing pin, bolt release, floor plate assembly, follower, trigger group screws, bands, bayonet lug, and stock are all matching. The stock has not been sanded and has an original K98K sling marked 1939 with maker.
The bore is excellent with no import mark on the barrel and the stock has not been cut. Still has most of the finish except for the butt plate. Erma stopped production of the K98K in 1941, and the serial number of this rifle is #194, making it a fairly early, hard to find variant.

The gun is all matching down to the screws, and cleaning rod. Nothing has been altered or changed since it left the field. Has the original blueing and is in excellent shape.
Gun has all birds intact and no import or Russian marks.

This is not a Russian capture, Yugo, or any of the other imported, mismatched, crap out there. Please don't waste your time or mine with offers not consistent with current, matching K98K prices.

MORE DETAILED PHOTOS: http://s1152.photobucket.com/user/lkh62891/library/Matching1939


Ultimate collectors item!
I hate to sell her but it's time to sell some items.

3,000 shipped to FFL dealer.
Contact me at Eig32-7thre2-48to1
